Compliance with these rules is essential to get any points for your
submission.
A violation of any of the following rules results in 0~points
for your submission.

\begin{enumerate}
\item All source files of your program(s) must compile via
  \begin{lstlisting}
$ gcc -std=c99 -pedantic -Wall -D_DEFAULT_SOURCE -D_BSD_SOURCE -D_SVID_SOURCE
                               -D_POSIX_C_SOURCE=200809L -g -c filename.c
  \end{lstlisting}
  without \emph{errors} and your program(s) must link without \emph{errors}.
  The compilation flags must be used in the Makefile.
  The feature test macros must not be bypassed
  (i.e., by undefining these macros or adding some in the C source code).
\item The functionality of the program(s) must conform to the assignment. The
  program(s) shall operate according to the specification/assignment given the
  test cases in the respective assignment.
\end{enumerate}
